hormonal actions of Sertoli cells and Leydig cells in male reproductive development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sertoli cells release anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone, promotes paramesonephric duct regression; Leydig cells release testosterone, promotes maintenance of mesonephric duct","Sertoli cells release testosterone, promotes paramesonephric duct regression; Leydig cells release anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone, promotes maintenance of mesonephric duct","Sertoli cells release anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone, promotes maintenance of mesonephric duct; Leydig cells release testosterone, promotes paramesonephric duct regression","Sertoli cells release testosterone, promotes maintenance of mesonephric duct; Leydig cells release anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone, promotes paramesonephric duct regression","Sertoli cells release anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone, promotes mesonephric duct regression; Leydig cells release testosterone, promotes maintenance of paramesonephric duct"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct relationship is that \u003Cstrong\u003ESertoli cells secrete anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone (AMH) which causes regression of the paramesonephric ducts, while Leydig cells secrete testosterone which maintains the mesonephric ducts\u003C/strong\u003E. This coordinated hormonal action is essential for proper male reproductive tract development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options incorrectly pair the cell types with their hormones or describe incorrect effects:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESertoli cells releasing testosterone\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - only Leydig cells produce testosterone\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeydig cells releasing AMH\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - only Sertoli cells produce AMH\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAMH promoting mesonephric duct maintenance\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - AMH causes paramesonephric duct regression\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETestosterone promoting paramesonephric duct maintenance\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - testosterone maintains mesonephric ducts\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe mesonephric ducts develop into male reproductive structures including the epididymis, vas deferens, and seminal vesicles, while the paramesonephric ducts regress in males but would otherwise form female reproductive structures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Sertoli cells secrete anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone (AMH) which causes regression of the paramesonephric (M\u00fcllerian) ducts in male embryos.","Leydig cells secrete testosterone which promotes development and maintenance of the mesonephric (Wolffian) ducts in male embryos.","The coordinated action of AMH and testosterone is essential for proper male reproductive tract development."],"references":["Al-Attar L, No\u00ebl K, Dutertre M, Belville C, Forest MG, Burgoyne PS, Josso N, Rey R. Hormonal and cellular regulation of Sertoli cell anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone production in the postnatal mouse. J Clin Invest. 1997 Sep 15;100(6):1335-43. doi: 10.1172/JCI119653. PMID: 9294098; PMCID: PMC508311.","Wilson D, Bordoni B. Embryology, Mullerian Ducts (Paramesonephric Ducts) [Updated 2023 Mar 6]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK557727/","Zirkin BR, Papadopoulos V. Leydig cells: formation, function, and regulation. Biol Reprod. 2018 Jul 1;99(1):101-111. doi: 10.1093/biolre/ioy059. PMID: 29566165; PMCID: PMC6044347.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"